Awhile back, I offered some basic raid training assistance to get people used to leading their own raids. Some great things came of it - Valathia became an aspiring, up-and-coming, ambitious young raid leader, and I got to meet lotsanew friends from CoS.<br>
<br>
This is a great basic skill to have. If there isn't an experienced raid leader on line, and your rare spawn is up - you may very well have to take charge.<br>
<br>
While raid leading isn't my forte - xp grinding is - I am MORE than happy to get you started. Basic stuff inviting people on the raid, giving directions. Makin sure everyone accounted for, loot, etc. How to yell - just kidding.<br>
<br>
I would like to see people get involved with some easier raids - maybe some of the beastlord ones for Empere's epic, the corrupt brownies for druids, heck - ask Arathain if you can lead Kael with him there to co-lead.<br>
<br>
